verses.text_plain: He that dasheth in pieces is come up before thy face: keep the munition, watch the way, make thy loins strong, fortify thy power mightily.
verses.verse_html:
1He that dasheth in pieces is come up before thy face: keep the munition, watch the way, make thy loins strong, fortify thy power mightily. ▼
▼ He…: or, The disperser, or, hammer

footnotes.body_text: ▼ He…: or, The disperser, or, hammer
footnotes.body_html: ▼ He…: or, The disperser, or, hammer

verses.text_plain: For the Lord hath turned away the excellency of Jacob, as the excellency of Israel: for the emptiers have emptied them out, and marred their vine branches.
verses.verse_html:
2For the Lord hath turned away the excellency of Jacob, as the excellency of Israel: for the emptiers have emptied them out, and marred their vine branches. ▼
▼ the excellency of Jacob…: or, the pride of Jacob as the pride, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the excellency of Jacob…: or, the pride of Jacob as the pride, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the excellency of Jacob…: or, the pride of Jacob as the pride, etc

verses.text_plain: The shield of his mighty men is made red, the valiant men are in scarlet: the chariots shall be with flaming torches in the day of his preparation, and the fir trees shall be terribly shaken.
verses.verse_html:
3The shield of his mighty men is made red, the valiant men are in scarlet: the chariots shall be with flaming torches in the day of his preparation, and the fir trees shall be terribly shaken. ▼
▼ in scarlet: or, dyed scarlet
 , ▼
▼ flaming: or, fiery

footnotes.body_html: ▼ in scarlet: or, dyed scarlet

verses.text_plain: The chariots shall rage in the streets, they shall justle one against another in the broad ways: they shall seem like torches, they shall run like the lightnings.
verses.verse_html:
4The chariots shall rage in the streets, they shall justle one against another in the broad ways: they shall seem like torches, they shall run like the lightnings. ▼
▼ they: Heb. their show

tokens.text: they shall justle one against another

footnotes.body_html: ▼ they: Heb. their show

verses.text_plain: He shall recount his worthies: they shall stumble in their walk; they shall make haste to the wall thereof, and the defence shall be prepared.
verses.verse_html:
5He shall recount his worthies: they shall stumble in their walk; they shall make haste to the wall thereof, and the defence shall be prepared. ▼
▼ worthies: or, gallants
 , ▼
▼ defence: Heb. covering, or, coverer

footnotes.body_html: ▼ defence: Heb. covering, or, coverer

verses.text_plain: The gates of the rivers shall be opened, and the palace shall be dissolved.
verses.verse_html:
6The gates of the rivers shall be opened, and the palace shall be dissolved. ▼
▼ dissolved: or, molten

verses.text_plain: And Huzzab shall be led away captive, she shall be brought up, and her maids shall lead her as with the voice of doves, tabering upon their breasts.
verses.verse_html:
7And Huzzab shall be led away captive, she shall be brought up, and her maids shall lead her as with the voice of doves, tabering upon their breasts. ▼
▼ Huzzab: or, that which was established, or, there was a stand made
 , ▼
▼ led…: or, discovered

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Huzzab: or, that which was established, or, there was a stand made
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Huzzab: or, that which was established, or, there was a stand made

verses.text_plain: But Nineveh is of old like a pool of water: yet they shall flee away. Stand, stand, shall they cry; but none shall look back.
verses.verse_html:
8But Nineveh is of old like a pool of water: yet they shall flee away. Stand, stand, shall they cry; but none shall look back. ▼
▼ of old: or, from the days that she hath been
 , ▼
▼ look back: or, cause them to turn

footnotes.body_html: ▼ look back: or, cause them to turn

verses.text_plain: Take ye the spoil of silver, take the spoil of gold: for there is none end of the store and glory out of all the pleasant furniture.
verses.verse_html:
9Take ye the spoil of silver, take the spoil of gold: for there is none end of the store and glory out of all the pleasant furniture. ▼
▼ for…: or, and their infinite store, etc
 , ▼
▼ pleasant…: Heb. vessels of desire

verses.text_plain: She is empty, and void, and waste: and the heart melteth, and the knees smite together, and much pain is in all loins, and the faces of them all gather blackness.
verses.verse_html: 10She is empty, and void, and waste: and the heart melteth, and the knees smite together, and much pain is in all loins, and the faces of them all gather blackness.

verses.text_plain: Where is the dwelling of the lions, and the feedingplace of the young lions, where the lion, even the old lion, walked, and the lion’s whelp, and none made them afraid?
verses.verse_html: 11Where is the dwelling of the lions, and the feedingplace of the young lions, where the lion, even the old lion, walked, and the lion’s whelp, and none made them afraid?

verses.text_plain: The lion did tear in pieces enough for his whelps, and strangled for his lionesses, and filled his holes with prey, and his dens with ravin.
verses.verse_html: 12The lion did tear in pieces enough for his whelps, and strangled for his lionesses, and filled his holes with prey, and his dens with ravin.

verses.text_plain: Behold, I am against thee, saith the Lord of hosts, and I will burn her chariots in the smoke, and the sword shall devour thy young lions: and I will cut off thy prey from the earth, and the voice of thy messengers shall no more be heard.
verses.verse_html: 13Behold, I am against thee, saith the Lord of hosts, and I will burn her chariots in the smoke, and the sword shall devour thy young lions: and I will cut off thy prey from the earth, and the voice of thy messengers shall no more be heard.
